hoice; the budget pick is reasonable if price is your primary constraint.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div style=\"margin:24px 0;\">\n<h3 style=\"margin-top:0;\">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>\n<div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px;\">\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9fb;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-weight:600;color:#290342;\">Should I prioritize CPU or GPU for general home/office use?</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#333;\">For everyday productivity, web browsing, and office work, CPU and RAM matter far more than graphics power - a dedicated GPU only becomes important for gaming, video editing, or 3D/creative work.</p>\n</div>\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9fb;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-weight:600;color:#290342;\">How much RAM is enough in 2026?</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#333;\">8GB is the bare minimum for basic browsing and office tasks; 16GB is comfortable for multitasking and most home/office workloads; 32GB or more is worth it for video editing, heavy multitasking, or running virtual machines.</p>\n</div>\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9fb;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-weight:600;color:#290342;\">Is it worth buying a prebuilt desktop versus building one myself?</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#333;\">A prebuilt saves time, includes a warranty on the whole system, and is usually cheaper than assembling equivalent parts individually thanks to bulk pricing - building your own mainly pays off if you want to hand-pick every component or need something highly specialized.</p>\n</div>\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9fb;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-weight:600;color:#290342;\">What should I check regarding upgrade room for the future?</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#333;\">Look at how many free RAM slots, drive bays, and expansion slots the case and motherboard leave open - a compact or all-in-one style desktop often has little to no upgrade room, while a mid-tower case usually leaves space to add storage or a graphics card later.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p><em>As an Amazon Associate, ChampionsReviews.com earns from qualifying purchases. All prices, ratings, and review counts shown are pulled directly from Amazon.com listings at the time of publishing and are subject to change. Pros, cons, and recommendations above are editorial analysis based on this listed data, not independent hands-on testing.</em></p>\n"
